This README file contains information on the contents of the
beignet layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
  layers: meta, meta-yocto, meta-yocto-bsp
  branch: jethro

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-intel
  layers: meta-intel
  branch: jethro


  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/meta-openembedded
  layers: meta-oe
  branch: jethro

Patches
=======

Please send patches to the maintainer:

California Sullivan <california.l.sullivan@intel.com>


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the beignet layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the beignet layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the beignet layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the beignet layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-intel \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openembedded/meta-oe \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-beignet \
    "


II. Misc
========

Add beignet to any project by adding "beignet" to IMAGE_INSTALL_append or as a dependency to another package.

Note that there is currently a build host limitation: it will only build on an x86_64 host.
